						<div class="postbody">Has everyone ever traced some pieces of the code in Battletoads ?
<br />The player moving is done just by changing the content of the same tiles (like in some SNES games like Chrono Trigger), and it's able to write a lot of stuff in $2007 in VBlank by doing :
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">pla&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ;3 cycles<br />sta $2007&nbsp; &nbsp; ;4 &#40;7 cycles per write&#41;<br />pla&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ;3<br />sta $2007&nbsp; &nbsp; ;4<br /><br />insted of :<br />lda $xxxx,X&nbsp; ;6 cycles<br />sta $2007&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;;4<br />inx&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;;2 &#40;12 cycles per write&#41;<br />etc...</div>
<br />... and I belived that all games with 32kb ROM bakswitching were technically gabrage...</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
